HEADWORD: Self-importance
<hw>Self`-im*por"tance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An
exaggerated estimate of one's own importance or merit, esp. as
manifested by the conduct or manners; self-conceit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-important</ent>⟦br⟧
